---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Federal Reserve Data | Net Worth Calculator" description="Learn about the Federal Reserve Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF) data methodology used by NetWorth.">
	<main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
		<header class="text-center mb-12 space-y-3">
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">
				About Our Federal Reserve Data
			</h1>
			<p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400 text-base md:text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto font-normal">
				Transparency & science-backed methodology behind our net worth percentile calculations.
			</p>
		</header>

		<div class="p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800/80 bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/60 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-xl text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300 space-y-8 font-normal leading-relaxed">
			<section class="space-y-2">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Federal Reserve Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF)</h2>
				<p>
					Our net worth percentile calculations are benchmarked against official triennial survey datasets published by the <strong>Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System</strong> (Survey of Consumer Finances). The SCF is widely considered the gold standard for analyzing household income, asset allocation, debt, and wealth distribution in the United States.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="space-y-2">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Median vs. Average Net Worth</h2>
				<p>
					Many financial news outlets report "Average Net Worth", which is heavily skewed upward by ultra-high-net-worth billionaires (top 0.1%). We emphasize <strong>Median Net Worth (50th Percentile)</strong> and granular percentile bands (10th, 25th, 50th, 75th, 90th, 95th, 99th) to give you an accurate, real-world comparison for your specific age group.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="space-y-2">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Primary Residence (Home Equity) Debate</h2>
				<p>
					Financial experts frequently debate whether home equity should be included in net worth. To solve this, our calculator includes a real-time <strong>Include Primary Residence</strong> toggle so you can measure both total net worth and liquid net worth.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="space-y-2">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">100% Client-Side Privacy</h2>
				<p>
					We do not store your financial data, collect email addresses, or transmit your net worth numbers to external servers. All math occurs 100% inside your Web browser.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
